        "kind": "pull_request",
        "title": "fix(gateway): preserve raw external session aliases",
        "body": "Closes #63005.\n\n## Behavior addressed\nStable raw external session keys such as `conversation:pair:user_a::user_b:space:space_123` should keep resolving to the same OpenClaw session after gateway canonicalization and nested `sessions_send` / agent activity.\n\n## Root cause\nThe gateway session-store migration path resolved the raw external key to the canonical `agent:<id>:...` key, copied the freshest entry to the canonical key, then pruned the raw key as a legacy alias. Future inbound traffic that still looked up the raw external key could create a fresh `sessionId`, splitting one logical conversation.\n\n## Fix\n`migrateAndPruneGatewaySessionStoreKey` now preserves non-agent structured raw external aliases while still pruning true legacy aliases. The regression test seeds the reported raw key shape and verifies the raw key and canonical key both retain `sess-raw`.\n\n## Evidence\nEnvironment: source checkout, Node `v22.22.0`, rebased onto current `upstream/main`.\n\nCurrent PR head: `87ecc789b95a4aeab08c89fa86d7c4eacc607cf7`  \nCurrent base checked: `3b5d30b5fdfd2d9e1e2f1c97242444467dce53c0`\n\nCommands run after rebase:\n\n```sh\npnpm docs:list\ngit rebase upstream/main\nnode scripts/run-vitest.mjs src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts\ngit diff --check upstream/main...HEAD\n./node_modules/.bin/oxfmt --check --threads=1 src/gateway/session-utils.ts src/gateway/session-utils.test.ts\n```\n\nFocused test result:\n\n```text\nTest Files  3 passed (3)\nTests       264 passed (264)\nDuration    24.17s\n```\n\nFormatter result:\n\n```text\nAll matched files use the correct format.\n```\n\nScreenshots: not applicable; this is backend session-store behavior. Terminal proof above covers the exact code path and regression.\n\n## Not tested\nLive third-party integration traffic was not exercised. The regression targets the deterministic session-store helper path implicated by the issue.\n",
